\textbf{Chain-of-Thought-LLM} --- \href{https://github.com/ClandestineAI/Chain-of-Thought-LLM}{github.com/ClandestineAI/Chain-of-Thought-LLM} \\
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
  \item Built a self-improving LLM pipeline using \textbf{loser-targeted training}: identifies bottom 25\% of samples by reasoning coherence, generates 10 complexity-escalation variants per loser via DeepSeek API, and iteratively trains toward GPT-5.2-class performance.
  \item Implemented \textbf{master scalar optimization}---a reasoning diversity metric (embedding dot-product with confidence penalty)---to measure generational progress; tracked improvements from 0.078 (GPT-4 class) targeting 0.018 (GPT-5.2 class).
  \item Engineered \textbf{grounded verification} eliminating hallucinations: code execution in sandboxed subprocesses, symbolic math solving via \textbf{SymPy}, and formal logic proofs via \textbf{Z3 theorem prover}; achieved 100\% verification rate on 40M+ training samples across 26 knowledge domains.
  \item Developed local embedding pipeline using \textbf{sentence-transformers} (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, 384-dim) for semantic similarity without external API dependency; integrated \textbf{Infini-Attention} mechanism for infinite-context transformers with fixed-size compressive memory.
  \item Built 6,000-line agentic CLI orchestrating end-to-end pipeline: data generation $\rightarrow$ verification $\rightarrow$ curriculum training (foundation/bridge/sophisticated phases) $\rightarrow$ benchmark evaluation (SWE-Bench, GPQA Diamond, AIME, ARC-AGI) $\rightarrow$ quality gates with automatic regression detection.
  \item Stack: \textbf{PyTorch}, Transformers, Unsloth, TRL/PEFT, Accelerate; deployed via Docker/Cloud Run with REST API serving.
\end{itemize}

